          "staff_generated_concept": "Staff Generated History"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "You came into Prince Benedic's employ in the early 20th century, a personal secretary and clerk who had a head for business for a Ventrue who clearly was old enough to not get modern industry. You were one of his large cadre of ghouls, but you imagined one of his most prized. Few of them could work as the financial intermediary for your domitor as you could, and when he departed the crowded courts of Mithras' England for America, he was sure to bring you with him. You followed him from city-to-city before he finally laid down roots in Las Vegas. Frankly, you thought the small city was flashy and gawdy and crawling with the gaucheness of the Giovanni, but Benedic wanted to set up his own, private domain, so someone had to work with them to make that happen. The Giovanni at least understood the usefulness of ghouls and you were one of the primary points between Benedict, Schlomo Rothstein and Dante Giovanni in establishing control and influence in Vegas. Benedic entrusted further to work directly with his Seneschal, the Nosferatu Geoffrey Montrose, service as Benedic's mouth piece and left hand in the domain.\n\nVegas might not have been London or DC, but you had power and influence in the domain, far more than most ghouls had, and you had the possibility of climbing still further had the Sabbat not interfered with the plans. A rogue couple wandered into Vegas and were captured on security cameras. They were subdued, temporarily, but when Montrose attempted to question one of them, he decided to break out by making an example out of you. You didn't even have time to react before you were split in two, spiked from stem to stern on a pillar of pure darkness, solid shadow. Through your guts and up your esophagus you could feel it, the deep, dark crawling cold and uncomprehending horror. Even now, when you think about it, you can still remember the pulling tide of it, and as your rival slammed you to the floor, you could see, just on the edges of your vision, the glittering, skittering shine of claws and the hissing whispers of something waiting there, watching, with hundreds of hungry eyes. As you sank into nothingness, you were certain that whatever it was, it was waiting there to devour your soul.\n\nWhen you awoke, one of Benedic's children, Alexandor Cantor, explained he had hurridly embraced you. You were far too valuable to just let die. You said nothing of what you saw, of what you experienced in those final moments. Instead, you did what you always did, kept calm and carried on. You have not forgotten, however, and it lurks there, just on the edges of your consciousness. If you look in shadows, sometimes, you think you can see whatever it is, waiting there, watching you, a predator, waiting for you to fall, watching for you to drop, so it can snag you and drag you down to the hell it was pulled out of.\n\nIt has been nearly 20 years since that night, and you've poured your nervous energies into furthering your former domitor's goals and interest. You single handedly ran Benedic's interest in Vegas until his kidnap and murder at the hands of human hunters five years ago. When Anthony Sands took the domain, you were left as the one Ventrue with all of the influence control and ties to Clan Giovanni. Sand knew you were far too valuable to give up and worked with you to further his own ambitious goals for the domain. Thing seemed to be going well, Vegas was finally starting to thrive after the economic hits of the financial crises and the loss of Benedic...until the hunters struck again. This time, they came in force, striking swiftly. You barely made it out with the aid of your own resources. You aren't even sure who else has made it. You fled to the closest and safest city in the area, Los Angeles. You have had ties to Prince Petrovna in the past and know that she would be welcoming. It's a place to regroup at least, to take stock of the situation and see what steps you need to take to survive - because you know what's waiting if you don't, and the hell you will allow yourself to taken like that."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Sire:",
          "column_2": "Alexandor Cantor",
          "column_3": "Reference: (If any)",
          "column_4": "Guide to the Camarilla/Guide to the Sabbat",
          "column_6": "Clan",
          "column_7": "Ventrue - Feeding Preference"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Embrace Date:",
          "column_2": 1999,
          "column_3": "Embrace Location:",
          "column_4": "Las Vegas",
          "column_6": "Generation",
          "column_7": "Ancilla *10"
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Who You Know",
          "column_2": "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Starting Goals",
          "column_2": "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "You left so quickly, you weren't able to figure out just what was going on in Vegas or who else survived. Find out who made it out of the city, if it has completely fallen and what the hell exactly happened."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "If you are relocating to Los Angeles, you need to set up shop in this domain. Figure out how the lay of the land lies influence wise in the city. Perhaps work to create a coterie of others who are refugess and opportunists who have to figure out how to restart all over again."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "The creature, whatever it is, is always watching and always threatening. Learn more about what it is and how to stop it - if at all possible - to try and circumvent your fate."
        },
        {
          "staff_generated_concept": "Player Amended History",
          "column_3": "Date Submited"
        }
      ]
    },
